Regular de-aging pills would make for a really boring SCP, no? What makes these pills special is that they do everything but.

Since all records and memories are changed, it does take a bit of investigation outside of controlled circumstances, but the discrepancies can be easily noticed if they're large enough. For example, if we find a grown man who insists - along with all his friends, colleagues, and official documents - that he's 8 years old, it doesn't take long to notice something's wrong.







